  {
    "sha": "fc86f29de0e3c208c5709491d03b0223097c4b22",
    "node_id": "C_kwDODmuHYdoAKGZjODZmMjlkZTBlM2MyMDhjNTcwOTQ5MWQwM2IwMjIzMDk3YzRiMjI",
    "commit": {
      "author": {
        "name": "Nate Cook",
        "email": "natecook@apple.com",
        "date": "2026-05-26T16:16:05Z"
      },
      "committer": {
        "name": "Nate Cook",
        "email": "natecook@apple.com",
        "date": "2026-05-26T16:16:05Z"
      },
      "message": "Revert source break in 1.8.0 `parse` methods\n\nThis removes the `async` overloads to `parse` and `parseAsRoot`\nthat caused a source break in 1.8.0, and introduces new names\nthat disambiguate the methods with `async` behavior. Instead of\ncalling the existing methods with the `await` keyword, users can\ncall `await asyncParse` or `await asyncParseAsRoot`.\n\nThis change also adds a validation step to the synchronous parsing\npath to check if an async completions function is called.\n\nUsers that have already updated their code to work around the\nsource break will revert to the old methods with this change,\nwhich will yield a \"No 'async' operations occur within 'await'\nexpression\" warning. They can remove the `await` keyword or update\nto call the async versions directly to fix the warning.",
      "tree": {
